.TH "nfs_iocounter_wait" 9 "nfs_iocounter_wait" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfs_iocounter_wait \- wait for i/o to complete
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nfs_iocounter_wait
.BI "(struct nfs_lock_context *l_ctx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "l_ctx" 12
nfs_lock_context with io_counter to use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
returns -ERESTARTSYS if interrupted by a fatal signal.
Otherwise returns 0 once the io_count hits 0.
